race.comment: MRS HARRIS (8) goes on top. She won her maiden easily first up at Stawell, good again at Geelong in a BM62 over 1755m second up when beaten half a length. Up to 2000m should suit ideally now and she sets up very well from the inside gate. DJOCKOVIC (2) was a surprise winner first up at Cranbourne in this grade over 1600m, scoring by a nose. Any extra ground will only suit better and he has to be respected. SUPER MIRAGE (4) is going okay without winning this time in, beaten as favourite here two back, a touch disappointing at Sandown Hillside last time. He's good enough to turn things around. LISA LASS (9) broke through for a narrow maiden win at Cranbourne last time out and can go on with it. CYCLONE HARMONY (1) doesn't win many but is going okay and has minor claims.
